  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Family Reunification and Re-integration of Street Children in Kinshasa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Poverty and accusations of witchcraft have driven 25,000 boys and girls onto Kinshasa&#x2019;s streets. They miss out on school and face violence from police and older youth. Many end up in gangs, drugs and sex work. This project runs a day centre for boys and a shelter for girls, providing meals, counselling, catch-up education and health care. The project works with police, market traders, church leaders and older youth, helping the young people to earn their own income. It reunites children with families where possible and gives their mothers a small business loan. As a result, people treat the children better, older youth are less likely to abuse them, and more children stay at home and in school.</narrative>
  </description>
